      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[codex] Scope Claude OAuth history by Keychain identity",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- scope successful Claude OAuth utilization samples to an opaque account key derived from the Keychain item's persistent reference\n- require the reference to remain stable before and after the fetch\n- route identityless OAuth samples to unscoped history when no fresh stable reference is available\n- preserve existing identity-keyed and unscoped history instead of merging potentially different accounts\n\n## Root cause\n\nOAuth snapshots contain no email or organization identity. The generic history resolver therefore reused the persisted preferred account bucket, causing a successful fetch after an account switch to be written into the previous account's history.\n\nThe new key is a namespaced SHA-256 hash of the Keychain persistent reference only. Access and refresh token material is never used or persisted.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `swift test --filter UsageStorePlanUtilizationClaudeIdentityTests` (12 tests)\n- `swift test --filter UsageStorePlanUtilizationTests` (41 tests)\n- `swift test --filter ClaudeOAuthCredentialsStoreTests` (18 tests)\n- `swift test --filter ClaudeResilienceTests` (13 tests)\n- `make check`\n- `git diff --check`\n\nCloses #1785\n",
        "branch": "codex/scope-claude-oauth-history",
